passages.text: August 28, 2025 09:46 AM GMT
FUJI OIL (2607) | Japan

Announced new mid- term plan (2025- 2027) on Aug 28, with briefing held from 3:30pm JST. BP target includes conservative price assumption for cocoa butter equivalents (CBE). Company is confident in progress made in Blommer structural reforms. No plans to invest in increasing CBE production capacity but there is room for volume growth.

F3/28 BP target in new MTP is \(\yen 45.0bn\) (vs. \(\yen 13.0bn\) for F3/25). Targets turn to profit at Blommer (vs. loss of \(\yen 31.0bn\) in F3/25), so effectively calls for flat profit growth aside from Blommer. Company explained during the briefing that it expects actual growth for mainstay businesses, but has made conservative assumptions for CBE prices.

Structural reforms at Blommer need adaptation to external environment, but production restructuring following the Chicago plant closure and inventory improvements for cacao products are steadily progressing, and the company has expressed confidence in returning to profitability.

The company expects cacao prices to remain high but not return to past levels, supporting steady demand for CBE as a substitute. However, it chose not to invest in expanding CBE production, despite operating at full capacity. President Omori explained that no opportunity loss is occurring. He added that by improving equipment (incl. using other product lines) and strengthening internal supply of intermediate materials a \(5 - 10\%\) increase in output is still possible.

Our price target is based on our F3/27e EPS of \(\yen 266\) and a fair- value multiple of 14.6x. This multiple is the F26e food industry avg of 17.0x multiplied by the stock's historical five- year industry- relative P/E value of 1.06x, less one standard deviation (0.86x). The discount takes account of the high volatility of Blommer earnings in recent years.
1) Setting in of black ink at Blommer, 2) CBE demand up more than expected and decision made to increase production, 3) stronger capital alliance, tie-ups in global expansion with Itochu Corp.
1) Blommer takes time to reach the black, 2) CBE demand declines, 3) palm oil costs rise, 4) weak chocolate, confectionery & bread demand due to economic downturn/higher raw material costs.
